President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in North Carolina due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Isaias. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate suffering and provide assistance for emergency measures. The assistance will include mass care, evacuation, and shelter support. The declaration covers various counties in North Carolina, as well as the Eastern Band of Cherokee Indians. Elizabeth Turner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.